## 9\. Common Pitfalls [Link to 9. Common Pitfalls](https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-01-30-request-trace-correlation/view\#9-common-pitfalls)

### Pitfall 1: Request ID Collisions [Link to Pitfall 1: Request ID Collisions](https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-01-30-request-trace-correlation/view\#pitfall-1-request-id-collisions)

**Problem**: Using sequential IDs or timestamp-only IDs that can collide.

```typescript
TypeScriptCopy
// BAD: Collisions likely under load
const requestId = `req-${Date.now()}`;

// GOOD: UUID has negligible collision probability
const requestId = randomUUID();
```

### Pitfall 2: Not Propagating Headers [Link to Pitfall 2: Not Propagating Headers](https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-01-30-request-trace-correlation/view\#pitfall-2-not-propagating-headers)

**Problem**: Downstream services don't receive correlation headers.

```typescript
TypeScriptCopy
// BAD: Headers lost in downstream call
const response = await fetch('http://service-b/api');

// GOOD: Propagate both request ID and trace context
const headers: Record<string, string> = {
  'x-request-id': req.requestId,
};
propagation.inject(context.active(), headers);
const response = await fetch('http://service-b/api', { headers });
```

### Pitfall 3: Missing Error Correlation [Link to Pitfall 3: Missing Error Correlation](https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-01-30-request-trace-correlation/view\#pitfall-3-missing-error-correlation)

**Problem**: Error responses don't include correlation IDs.

```typescript
TypeScriptCopy
// BAD: No way to trace this error
res.status(500).json({ error: 'Something went wrong' });

// GOOD: Always include correlation in errors
res.status(500).json({
  error: 'Something went wrong',
  requestId: req.requestId,
  traceId: req.correlationIds.traceId,
  timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
});
```

### Pitfall 4: Inconsistent Header Names [Link to Pitfall 4: Inconsistent Header Names](https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-01-30-request-trace-correlation/view\#pitfall-4-inconsistent-header-names)

**Problem**: Different services use different header names.

```typescript
TypeScriptCopy
// Inconsistent (confusing)
// Service A: X-Request-ID
// Service B: X-Correlation-ID
// Service C: Request-Id

// GOOD: Standardize across all services
const REQUEST_ID_HEADER = 'x-request-id';
const TRACE_ID_HEADER = 'x-trace-id';
```

### Pitfall 5: Not Logging Correlation IDs [Link to Pitfall 5: Not Logging Correlation IDs](https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-01-30-request-trace-correlation/view\#pitfall-5-not-logging-correlation-ids)

**Problem**: Logs exist but can't be connected to traces.

```typescript
TypeScriptCopy
// BAD: No correlation
console.log('Payment processed');

// GOOD: Always include correlation
console.log(JSON.stringify({
  message: 'Payment processed',
  request_id: req.requestId,
  trace_id: req.correlationIds.traceId,
  span_id: req.correlationIds.spanId,
}));
```

